         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">June 17. 64 ¶ Dear Dr Mueller ¶  ¶ The bearer of this is a gentleman who is visiting Australia for his health, with his sister. ¶  — Mr &amp; Miss Hodgson's mother is a very near neighbour of ours, indeed...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.06.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">June 17. 64</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The bearer of this is a gentleman who is visiting Australia for his health, with his sister.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">James and Elizabeth Hodgson (aged 18 and 25 respectively) arrived in Melbourne per <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lincolnshire</seg> on 17 September 1864 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">(Index to Unassisted Inward Passenger Lists to Victoria 1852-1923</seg>).</p>
               </note> — Mr &amp; Miss Hodgson's mother is a very near neighbour of ours, indeed dwells on the premises, the Honble Mrs H. having charge of Kew Palace.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Hodgson has kindly taken charge of the <name key="Papyrus">Papyrus</name> for you &amp; will I hope transport it alive this time. Two boxes from Mr Bentham went for you two days ago from this.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Oldfield is still in this Country &amp; has not made up his mind what to do.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My father is remaining well &amp; desires his kindest regards; he is very busy at his Synopsis Filicum<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">W. Hooker &amp; Baker (1865-8).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever my dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Most sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Papyrus">Papyrus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
